====================Command Line Arguments============
1. When you run a Java program, you can pass extra inputs directly in the command line (terminal).

2. These inputs are called command line arguments.

3. They are passed to the program as an array of strings (String[] args) in the main method.

4. You can use these arguments inside your program to affect how it runs.


code :
public class AddStrings {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        if (args.length < 2) {
            System.out.println("Please provide two strings as arguments.");
            return;
        }
        
        String str1 = args[0];
        String str2 = args[1];
        
        String result = str1 + str2;
        System.out.println("Concatenated string: " + result);
    }
}


steps to run: 

1.compile -> javac AddStrings.java

2.run->  java AddStrings Hello World
3.output-> Concatenated string: HelloWorld


